title: Episode 127: Jonathon Aslay – What Is Self Love Anyway?
description:
In this episode, Robbie interviews Jonathon Aslay, a dating and relationship expert for mid-life people. They discuss a topic rarely mentioned, but hugely important, and the number one emotional health issue facing singles today: a soul-deep lack of self worth and self love.

Show Notes:

Jonathon’s story of turning 40, going through a divorce and then going on over 100 dates in a year… (03:00)

“What The Heck Is Self Love Anyway?” (09:30)

The difference between self love and self worth… (10:30)

Can you communicate your feelings in a relationship without causing a fight? (12:00)

The problem with dating under the premise of chemistry… (17:00)
What emotional maturity really means and why it’s the secret to healthy relationships… (17:30)

The “Paradox of Choice” as it relates to choosing the right woman for a long term relationship or marriage… (23:30)

The role that values play in a relationship and how to tell if you share the same ones… (25:00)

How to tell if you and your partner have blend-able lifestyles… (26:00)

 The 4 foundations of a successful relationship… (26:45)

How to tell if your partner is emotionally mature… (28:00)

How Jonathon overcame losing his 7-figure net worth at the age of 40… (31:15)

How to be a grown up around immature people and win in relationships… (37:30)

Overcoming the grief of losing his nineteen-year-old son and how he was able to cope and reconcile… (41:00)

What happens when you lean into adversity… (45:30)
The mind, the body, the spirit, and your emotions equals “The …” (48:30)

How to create a team of people you talk to on a regular basis to help you improve and grow… (52:00)

A conversational technique that allows for venting, processing, and witnessing without annoying the person listening to you… (54:00)

Links-

JonathonAslay.com/love
“8 Dates” – Dr. John Gottman
“Untethered Soul” – Michael Singer
“Return to Love” – Marianne Williamson
“The Four Agreements” – Don Michael Ruiz
“The 12 Rules For Life” – Jordan B. Peterson  
The Warrior Weekend by The Mankind Project
Jonathon’s Aslay’s Facebook

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.
